{"id": "715a5991d4f9", "timestamp": "2026-04-09T15:35:15.377194", "error_type": "Session Error", "error_message": "Automatic session resume failed, so sending the status directly.", "severity": "warning", "file_location": "unknown", "language": "unknown", "context_summary": "A Telegram bot named 'hedgeclaw' reported an automatic session resume failure. The bot appears to be a monitoring/coding assistant ('Blackbox') that detects errors on screen and applies fixes. The session resume failure caused it to fall back to sending status directly. The bot also mentions recent fixes including feedback loop prevention, full error message sending, and a Fix Queue cron job running every 5 minutes.", "fix": "**Cause:** The bot's session state (likely stored in a file or memory) became invalid or expired, and the resume logic lacks proper error handling to silently recover and reinitialize a fresh session.\n\n**Fix:** Wrap the session resume call in a try/catch that clears the corrupted/expired session data and initiates a new session automatically, rather than falling back to a direct status send:\n\n```python\ntry:\n    await client.connect()\n    if not await client.is_user_authorized():\n        raise Se", "screenshot_b64": "iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAA8AAAAIcCAIAAAC2P1AsAAEAAElEQVR42uyddZgdRdaHz6lqu37veNzdCBICgeDBdXEWWWxx/3B3Z9EAC8vi7m4hhARIAhHi7pPxmTtXu7uqzvfHnYQkBAjJAAlbL/08ZPpWe3X3r08dwe6DdgaNRqPRaDQajUazYTB9CjQajUaj0Wg0", "notified": false}
