{"id": "ab74a0aefd4d", "timestamp": "2026-04-09T15:36:09.887269", "error_type": "Bot/Automation Failure", "error_message": "Automatic session resume failed, so sending the status directly. Agent was aborted. Queue has 2 entries that shouldn't be there \u2014 I cleared it before restarting. Old entries from a previous session.", "severity": "critical", "file_location": "N/A", "language": "Bot/Automation Framework (likely Python or Node.js)", "context_summary": "A Telegram bot conversation shows multiple failure indicators: automatic session resume failed, an agent was aborted, a watcher queue had stale entries from a previous session, and the user is angrily demanding the bot stop using 'Blackbox API' for its tasks. The bot appears to be a coding/automation assistant experiencing session management and queue corruption issues.", "fix": "**Cause:** The watcher queue is persisted to disk/Redis without a session-scoped key or TTL, so stale entries from the previous session survive restarts and replay into the new session, causing the agent to abort when it tries to resume an invalid state.\n\n**Fix:** Namespace the queue key with a unique session ID (e.g., `queue:{session_id}`) generated fresh on each bot start, or flush the queue atomically on startup with `DEL queue:*` / `queue.clear()` *before* the agent initializes \u2014 and separat", "screenshot_b64": "iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAA8AAAAIcCAIAAAC2P1AsAAEAAElEQVR42uyddZwcRdrHn6equnt81jfJZuNuECRIggUI7n44h7sfepBD7oVDDjvkOOBwd5cQQkIIIUbcfbNuo91dVc/7x2xCFEKyCSFX35vPsZlpra6u/vVTj2C3HfYCg8FgMBgMBoPBsHEw0wQGg8Fg", "notified": true}
